<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Proceeding" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Proceeding,</orth> subst. 1) doing, action, course taken: <cit><quote>his --s teach thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 406" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 406</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>like the --s of a drunken brain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 406" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 406</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>I'll cross Thurio's dull p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.6.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 6, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and here an engine fit for my p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.138" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 138</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>determine our --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.97" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 97</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to these violent --s all my neighbours shall cry aim,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 2, 44</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the straitness of his p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.270" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 270</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>unpregnant and dull to all --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 24</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.358" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 358</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.4.50" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 4, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 1, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.214" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 214</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.1.114" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.133" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 3, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.110" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.5.103" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.66" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.403" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 403</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.108" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.18" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.7.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 7, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 163</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 2, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.322" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 322</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.233" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 233</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 65</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 4.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 3, 25</bibl>.<lb />2) process, course: <cit><quote>what plain p. is more plain than this?</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 2, 53</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I have an interest in your hate's p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 193</bibl></cit>.
